R htmlwidgets-D3 and Canvas Express

Ehson Ghandehari

6/13/2017

R Markdown

The purpose of this Markdown document is to utilized some of the R htmlwidgets. In this document the iris dataset were used for visualization. We use pairsD3, and canvasXpress for graphing.

Including Plots

library(pairsD3)
data(iris)
require(pairsD3)
pairsD3(iris[,1:4],group=iris[,5])


Figure 1: Presenting the Iris data set in three-dimension pair(faces). 

library(canvasXpress)
data <- t(iris[,1:4])
varAnnot <- as.matrix(iris[,5])
colnames(varAnnot) <- "Species"
canvasXpress(t(data), varAnnot=varAnnot, graphType='Scatter3D', colorBy='Species')


Figure 2: Presenting the Iris data based on three variables: Sepal length, sepal width, and petal width.
